  <title translate="true">Tip #66</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If one provides a class-side </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">#initialize</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> method then it is automatically executed when the class is installed as part of a package. Remember, typically one does not supersend class-side </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">#initialize</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> methods as this can cause problems with duplicate initialisation.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If your class needs to perform some operations so that it can be cleanly removed from the image then you should supply an </text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">#uninitialize</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> class-side method too. This will be automatically called when a package containing the class is unloaded from the image.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
